ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.

ElementDescription: Sex of subject at birth
Notes: M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ElementDescription: My child often seems content to play alone.
Notes: 1 = Not A lot; 2 = Infrequently; 3 = Sometimes; 4 = Frequently;   5 = A Lot

ElementDescription: My child seems to want to play with other children, but is sometimes nervous to.
Notes: 1 = Not A lot; 2 = Infrequently; 3 = Sometimes; 4 = Frequently;   5 = A Lot

ElementDescription: My child is just as happy to play quietly by his/herself than to play with a group of children.
Notes: 1 = Not A lot; 2 = Infrequently; 3 = Sometimes; 4 = Frequently;   5 = A Lot

ElementDescription: My child is happiest when playing with other children. (reverse scored)
Notes: 5 = Not A lot; 4 = Infrequently; 3 = Sometimes; 2 = Frequently;   1 = A Lot

ElementDescription: My child will turn down social initiations from other children because he/she is 'shy'.
Notes: 1 = Not A lot; 2 = Infrequently; 3 = Sometimes; 4 = Frequently;   5 = A Lot

ElementDescription: My child often approaches other children to initiate play. (reverse scored)
Notes: 5 = Not A lot; 4 = Infrequently; 3 = Sometimes; 2 = Frequently;   1 = A Lot

ElementDescription: My child 'hovers' near where other children are playing, without joining in.
Notes: 1 = Not A lot; 2 = Infrequently; 3 = Sometimes; 4 = Frequently;   5 = A Lot

ElementDescription: My child rarely initiates play activities with other children.
Notes: 1 = Not A lot; 2 = Infrequently; 3 = Sometimes; 4 = Frequently;   5 = A Lot

ElementDescription: If given the choice, my child prefers to play with other children rather than alone. (reverse scored)
Notes: 5 = Not A lot; 4 = Infrequently; 3 = Sometimes; 2 = Frequently;   1 = A Lot

ElementDescription: My child often watches other children play without approaching them.
Notes: 1 = Not A lot; 2 = Infrequently; 3 = Sometimes; 4 = Frequently;   5 = A Lot

ElementDescription: Although he/she appears to desire to play with others, my child is sometimes anxious about interacting with other children.
Notes: 1 = Not A lot; 2 = Infrequently; 3 = Sometimes; 4 = Frequently;   5 = A Lot
